cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.CY, cs.MM

The paper focuses on the feasibility of touch gesture behavioural biometrics for implicit authentication of users on a smartglass (Google Glass). This involves the use of machine learning classifiers to identify users based on their touch gestures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), which deals with authentication and security issues. 

The paper also involves the use of wearable devices (smartglasses) and touch gestures, which are relevant to the categories cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.MM (Multimedia). 

The use of classifiers and machine learning algorithms to identify users based on touch gestures also falls under the category cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

Finally, the paper involves the use of data analysis and statistical methods to evaluate the performance of the system, which is relevant to the category cs.CY (Computers and Society).
